### What problem does this feature solve?
`[Before]`
```javascript
export function isPromise (val: any): boolean {
  return (
    isDef(val) &&
    typeof val.then === 'function' &&
    typeof val.catch === 'function' 
  )
}
```

`[After]`
```javascript
export function isPromise (val: any): boolean {
  return (
    isDef(val) &&
    val instanceof Promise ||
    Promise.prototype.isPrototypeOf(val)
  )
}
```

The Before 'isPromise' function returns true when 
```javascript
    isPromise({then: function(){}, catch: function(){}}) // true(this is not what we want.)
```

So The After 'isPromise' function checks instance's own constructor and prototype chain.

### What does the proposed API look like?
```javascript
export function isPromise (val: any): boolean {
  return (
    isDef(val) &&
    val instanceof Promise ||
    Promise.prototype.isPrototypeOf(val)
  )
}
```

